FAQ

Here are some of the questions we receive frequently. If you have ulterior questions contact us through our Telegram channel

Accordion Item 1
What is tree Defi?

Tree Defi is a yield farming protocol built on the Binance Smart Chain. Our focus is stable tokenomics through a two token system. Moreover, one third of the deposit fees on our platform will be used to plant trees in real life. Our donations will have proof of purchase and will be trackable by users.

What is yield farming?

Yield farming is an innovative DeFi concept where users stake their crypto assets in order to receive returns. For more info on yield farming, you can start with this article.

How do i use Tree Defi?

You can join our Yield Farm by converting your assets into our tokens and depositing them into our farms and pools. You will receive rewards that are higher or lower depending on the investment amount you've put in the project. If you are already a DeFi veteran, go ahead to app.treedefi.com and try it out. If you are new make sure you educate yourself on the risks and take proper advice. Here is a good article that will introduce you to Yield Farming

Is it safe to use Tree Defi?

We have been audited by TechRate and Soteria (before starting our partnership), therefore our code has been tested for any weaknesses.

We have also locked the initial liquidity and our dev funds for a total of 6 months.

But we really think the best way to build trust is by interacting with us directly through Telegram, we'll always be there to help you and answer any questions.

What are TREE and SEED token?

TREE is a capped token of the TreeDefi platform. Its current supply is 16001 TREE.

SEED is the uncapped counterpart, that uses deflationary and burn mechanisms to remain stable.

For more details, please visit our documentation page: docs.treedefi.com
